KRANSKOP, KwaZulu-Natal - Newly-appointed finance minister Nhlanhla Nene is ready to hit the ground running. Speaking exclusively to eNCA from his home in KwaZulu-Natal, Nene said things are looking up for the country’s struggling economy. Nene spoke about the so-called "Cyril effect", a possible credit downgrade by Moody's at the end of March, and whether land expropriation without compensation will scare off investors. Watch the interview above. READ: SA's economy to get boost after Cabinet reshuffle: Reuters poll  eNCA